nsproxy tests
====================

This directory contains integration tests for nsproxy. The integration test
suite consists of three core components:

1. Target Server
   A ping-pong server (tcp_pingpong.py, udp_pingpong.py) listens on port 37777.
   It receives data from the client and sends a response back.

2. Proxy Servers
   Support for v2ray, sing-box, or shadowsocks-rust as proxy server.
   One proxy server instance listens on all 4 ports:
   - SOCKS5 on 31080 (no auth) and 31081 (auth)
   - HTTP on 38080 (no auth) and 38081 (auth)

3. Application
   The ping-pong client that runs inside a network namespace via nsproxy.
   Its traffic is captured by nsproxy and forwarded through the proxy server.


REQUIREMENTS
----------

 - v2ray OR sing-box OR shadowsocks-rust (installed and in PATH)
 - Python 3 with pytest


USAGE
----------

Run following commands in the project root directory, not in tests/

To run all tests:

   pytest -v tests/

Note: nsproxy runs in verbose mode (`-vvv`) only when pytest is run with
verbose mode (`-v`).


VALGRIND TESTING
----------------

To run tests with Valgrind memory checker, use the `--valgrind` option:

   pytest -v tests/ --valgrind

The project should be compiled without Address Sanitizer (ASan). Use the
following build command:

   cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="-fno-omit-frame-pointer"
   cmake --build build
